HEADWORD: Subminister
<hw>Sub*min"is*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>subministrare</ets>, <ets>subministratum</ets>. See <er>Sub-</er>,
and <er>Ministre</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>To supply; to
afford.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir M. Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subminister</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Subminister
<hw>Sub*min"is*ter</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be subservient; to be
useful.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Our passions . . .
<xex>subminister</xex> to the best and worst purposes.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>L'EStrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subministrant</ent>⟦br⟧
